description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a dynamic and highly motivated individual to strategically lead on enhancing the care of people and their families living with dementia at Portsmouth Hospitals University NHS Trust, supported by the Deputy Chief Nurse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful post holder will provide visible, credible leadership that will ensure our patients receive the highest standards of care. This will include the development of a dementia strategy and an education programme that supports our staff to deliver excellent care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have extensive experience in leading services for people with dementia and a proven track record in making improvements for these patients and their families.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return you will work with great staff and be part of an enthusiastic Quality and Safety Team. You will be fully supported to develop personally to deliver your role and further your personal ambitions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details please contact Tina Hetherington on 02392 286000 ext 6498 or via email at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tina.Hetherington@porthosp.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: &lt;/strong&gt;Wednesday 11th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: &lt;/strong&gt;Friday 20th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
